<h2><a name="TOC-The-purpose-of-the-Organisation-theme"></a>The purpose of the Organisation theme</h2>
<div></div>
<div class="sites-codeblock sites-codesnippet-block">
<div><code>The purpose of the Organisation theme is to define and establish the project's structure of accountability and responsibilities (the who).</code></div>
<div></div>
</div>
<br>
<div>The defined organisational structure should enable effective <b>governance and decision making</b>.</div>
<div><br>
</div>
<div>The structure should:</div>
<div>
<ul><li>Have Business, User and Supplier stakeholder representation</li>
<li>Enable governance to be achieved by defining responsibilities for <b>directing</b>, <b>managing</b> and <b>delivering</b> the project and accountability at each level</li>
<li>Be reviewed throughout the project to ensure that it remains effective</li>
<li>Define responsibilities and strategy for communication with stakeholders (employees, protesters etc).</li></ul>
<span style="background-color:transparent;font-size:1em;line-height:1.5">&nbsp;</span></div>
<h2><a name="TOC-How-the-Organisation-theme-supports-the-defined-roles-and-responsibilities-principle"></a>How the Organisation theme supports the defined roles and responsibilities principle</h2>
<div>The defined roles and responsibilities principle is stated on the <a href="/">Overview page</a>.</div>
<div><br>
</div>
<div>The Organisation theme:</div>
<div>
<ul><li>Defines <b>roles</b> and each role has <b>responsibilities</b></li>
<li>Roles and responsibilities are agreed with the appropriate level within the hierarchy</li>
<li>The three primary stakeholder interests <b>Business (Executive)</b>, <b>User (Senior User(s))</b> and <b>Supplier (Senior Supplier(s))&nbsp;</b>form the Project Board in the Organisation theme</li></ul>
<br>
</div>
